So i listen to a lot of synthwave. Born in 70. I know the genre well. I have listened to... i dont know how many thousands of songs across all sub-genres of synth over my lifetime. And obviously there are so many amazing artist's with so many amazing songs. But i will admit...sitting at the top of my list...covering my entire life of listening to synth...is this easy little song called Levitate. The first time i heard it i cried. I dont know why. It could be a U2 connection with me. With or without you vibe. A song that i dedicate to my brother who passed in the early 90s. I dont know. This song is so simple. So clean. Just a build up of emotions. Each layer and volume increase generates emotion from deep down. Then when the drums hit and balling. Not many songs cleanse me emotionally. But Levitate is one of them. And its probably my favorite synthwave song of all time.
One of the best songs of this genre hands down & also my favourite song of that year.
